1510
01:39:41,870 --> 01:39:47,050
As soon as possible, a group of three heavy
cruisers, armed with all the inventions that

1511
01:39:47,050 --> 01:39:53,489
had been discovered, the atostor power system,
perfectly conducting power leads, the terrible

1512
01:39:53,489 --> 01:39:56,050
UV ray, started out.

1513
01:39:56,050 --> 01:39:58,320
The scouts got there first.

1514
01:39:58,320 --> 01:40:03,619
Cameras were grinding steadily, with long
range telescopic lenses, delicate instruments

1515
01:40:03,619 --> 01:40:07,989
probed and felt and caught their fingers in
the fields of the giant fleet.

1516
01:40:07,989 --> 01:40:15,810
At ten-second intervals, giant ships popped
into being, and glided smoothly toward Jupiter.

1517
01:40:15,810 --> 01:40:18,780
Then the cruisers arrived.

1518
01:40:18,780 --> 01:40:22,690
They halted at a respectful distance, and
waited.

1519
01:40:22,690 --> 01:40:26,099
The Miran ships plowed on undisturbed.

1520
01:40:26,099 --> 01:40:31,030
Simultaneously, from the three leaders, terrific
neutron rays shot out.

1521
01:40:31,030 --> 01:40:36,909
The paraffin block walls stopped those—and
the cruisers started to explain their feelings

1522
01:40:36,909 --> 01:40:37,980
on the subject.

1523
01:40:37,980 --> 01:40:42,900
They were the IP-J-37, 39, and 42.

1524
01:40:42,900 --> 01:40:47,710
The 37 turned up the full power of the UV
ray.

1525
01:40:47,710 --> 01:40:53,909
The terrific beam of ultra-violet energy struck
the second Miran ship, and the spot it touched

1526
01:40:53,909 --> 01:41:00,239
exploded into incandescence, burned white-hot—and
puffed out abruptly as the air pressure within

1527
01:41:00,239 --> 01:41:03,340
blew the molten metal away.

1528
01:41:03,340 --> 01:41:05,840
The Mirans were startled.

1529
01:41:05,840 --> 01:41:09,700
This was not the type of thing Gresth Gkae
had warned them of.

1530
01:41:09,700 --> 01:41:14,810
Gresth Gkae himself frowned as the sudden
roar of the machines of his ship rose in the

1531
01:41:14,810 --> 01:41:15,970
metal walls.

1532
01:41:15,970 --> 01:41:22,079
A stream of ten-inch atomic bombs shrieked
out of their tubes, fully glowing green things

1533
01:41:22,079 --> 01:41:26,400
floated out more slowly, and immediately waxed
brilliant.

1534
01:41:26,400 --> 01:41:30,440
Gamma ray bombs—but they could be guarded
against—

1535
01:41:30,440 --> 01:41:37,020
The three Solarian cruisers were washed in
such frightful flame as they had never imagined.

1536
01:41:37,020 --> 01:41:43,099
Streams of atomic bombs were exploding soundlessly,
ineffectively in space, not thirty feet from

1537
01:41:43,099 --> 01:41:47,030
them as they felt the sudden resistance of
the magnetic shields.

1538
01:41:47,030 --> 01:41:50,730
Hopefully, the 39 probed with her neutron
gun.

1539
01:41:50,730 --> 01:41:56,070
Nothing happened save that several gamma ray
bombs went off explosively, and all the atomic

1540
01:41:56,070 --> 01:41:59,270
bombs in its path exploded at once.

1541
01:41:59,270 --> 01:42:02,730
Gresth Gkae knew what that meant.

1542
01:42:02,730 --> 01:42:04,199
Neutron beam guns.

1543
01:42:04,199 --> 01:42:08,230
Then this race was more intelligent than he
had believed.

1544
01:42:08,230 --> 01:42:10,619
They had not had them before.

1545
01:42:10,619 --> 01:42:15,860
Had he perhaps given them too much warning
and information?

1546
01:42:15,860 --> 01:42:20,059
There was a sudden, deeper note in the thrumming
roar of the great ship.

1547
01:42:20,059 --> 01:42:24,850
Eagerly Gresth Gkae watched—and sighed in
relief.

1548
01:42:24,850 --> 01:42:28,489
The nearer of the three enemy ships was crumbling
to dust.

1549
01:42:28,489 --> 01:42:32,789
Now the other two were beginning to become
blurred of outline.

1550
01:42:32,789 --> 01:42:36,170
They were fleeing—but oh, so slowly.

1551
01:42:36,170 --> 01:42:41,199
Easily the greater ship chased them down,
till only floating dust, and a few small pieces

1552
01:42:41,199 --> 01:42:42,199
of—

1553
01:42:42,199 --> 01:42:45,869
Gresth Gkae shrieked in pain, and horror.

1554
01:42:45,869 --> 01:42:49,309
The destroyed ships had fought in dying.

1555
01:42:49,309 --> 01:42:54,860
All space seemed to blossom out with a terrible
light, a light that wrapped around them, and

1556
01:42:54,860 --> 01:42:56,590
burned into him, and through him.

1557
01:42:56,590 --> 01:43:03,320
His eyes were dark and burning lumps in his
head, his flesh seemed crawling, stinging—he

1558
01:43:03,320 --> 01:43:08,599
was being flayed alive—in shrieking agony
he crumpled to the floor.

1559
01:43:08,599 --> 01:43:13,550
Hospital attachés came to him, and injected
drugs.

1560
01:43:13,550 --> 01:43:15,980
Slowly torturing consciousness left him.

1561
01:43:15,980 --> 01:43:22,300
The doctors began working over his horribly
burned body, shuddering inwardly as the protective,

1562
01:43:22,300 --> 01:43:26,560
feather-like covering of his skin loosened,
and dropped from his body.

1563
01:43:26,560 --> 01:43:29,670
Tenderly they lowered him into a bath of chemicals—

1564
01:43:29,670 --> 01:43:37,360
"The terrible light which caused so much damage
to our men," reported a physicist, "was analyzed,

1565
01:43:37,360 --> 01:43:40,850
and found to have some extraordinary lines.

1566
01:43:40,850 --> 01:43:46,830
It was largely mercury-vapor spectrum, but
the spectrum of mercury-atoms in an impossibly

1567
01:43:46,830 --> 01:43:48,360
strained condition.

1568
01:43:48,360 --> 01:43:54,340
I would suggest that great care be used hereafter,
and all men be equipped with protective masks

1569
01:43:54,340 --> 01:43:56,469
when observations are needed.

1570
01:43:56,469 --> 01:44:01,570
This sun is very rich in the infra-X-rays
