2248
02:30:01,920 --> 02:30:03,210
the idea."

2249
02:30:03,210 --> 02:30:07,439
"Yes, but only two ships in the system compare
with them in size."

2250
02:30:07,439 --> 02:30:13,260
"Sorry—but I didn't build the IP fleet,
and there are lots of tungsten and beryllium

2251
02:30:13,260 --> 02:30:14,260
on Earth.

2252
02:30:14,260 --> 02:30:15,260
Enough anyway."

2253
02:30:15,260 --> 02:30:17,729
"Will they use that beam on the fort?

2254
02:30:17,729 --> 02:30:19,630
And can't we use the thing on them?"

2255
02:30:19,630 --> 02:30:23,250
"They won't and we won't—though we could.

2256
02:30:23,250 --> 02:30:27,540
A bank of those new million watt tubes—perhaps
a hundred of them—and we'd have a pretty

2257
02:30:27,540 --> 02:30:31,500
effective heater—but an awful waste of power.

2258
02:30:31,500 --> 02:30:33,680
I've got something better."

2259
02:30:33,680 --> 02:30:34,680
"New?"

2260
02:30:34,680 --> 02:30:35,680
"Somewhat.

2261
02:30:35,680 --> 02:30:40,740
I've found out how to make the mirror field
in a plate of metal, instead of a block.

2262
02:30:40,740 --> 02:30:43,729
Come on to the lab, and I'll show you."

2263
02:30:43,729 --> 02:30:45,689
"What's the advantage?

2264
02:30:45,689 --> 02:30:48,189
Oh—weight saved, and silver metal saved."

2265
02:30:48,189 --> 02:30:51,580
"A lot more than that, Mac.

2266
02:30:51,580 --> 02:30:52,580
Watch."

2267
02:30:52,580 --> 02:30:58,090
At the laboratory, the new apparatus looked
immensely lighter and simpler than the old.

2268
02:30:58,090 --> 02:31:05,300
The atostor, the ionizer, and the twin ion-projectors
were as before, great, rigid, metal structures

2269
02:31:05,300 --> 02:31:10,319
that would maintain the meeting point of the
