2273
02:31:23,140 --> 02:31:24,140
in thickness.

2274
02:31:24,140 --> 02:31:29,489
It was mounted in a framework of complex,
stout metal braces.

2275
02:31:29,489 --> 02:31:35,100
Kendall started the ion-flame at low intensity,
so the UV beam was little more than a spotlight.

2276
02:31:35,100 --> 02:31:38,609
"You missed the point, Mac.

2277
02:31:38,609 --> 02:31:41,080
Now—watch that tungsten-beryllium plate.

2278
02:31:41,080 --> 02:31:43,350
I'll hold the power steady.

2279
02:31:43,350 --> 02:31:49,689
It's an eighteen-inch beam—and now the energy
is just sufficient to heat that tungsten plate

2280
02:31:49,689 --> 02:31:51,540
to bright red.

2281
02:31:51,540 --> 02:31:52,960
But—"

2282
02:31:52,960 --> 02:31:58,609
Kendall turned over a small rheostat control—and
abruptly the eighteen-inch diameter spot on

2283
02:31:58,609 --> 02:32:04,750
the tungsten-beryllium plate began contracting;
it contracted till it was a blazing, sparkling

2284
02:32:04,750 --> 02:32:09,880
spot of molten incandescence less than an
inch across!

2285
02:32:09,880 --> 02:32:13,600
"That's the advantage of focus.

2286
02:32:13,600 --> 02:32:18,040
At this distance of a few hundred feet with
a small beam I can do that.

2287
02:32:18,040 --> 02:32:23,510
With a twenty-foot beam, I can get a two-foot
spot at a distance of nearly ten miles!

2288
02:32:23,510 --> 02:32:27,430
That means that the receiving end will have
the pleasure of handling one hundred times

2289
02:32:27,430 --> 02:32:30,109
the energy concentration.

2290
02:32:30,109 --> 02:32:32,980
That would punch a hole through most anything.

2291
02:32:32,980 --> 02:32:34,939
All you have to do is focus it.

2292
02:32:34,939 --> 02:32:39,170
The trouble being, if it's out of focus the
advantage is more than lost.

2293
02:32:39,170 --> 02:32:44,330
So if there's any question about getting the
focus, we'll get along without it."

2294
02:32:44,330 --> 02:32:47,290
"A real help, if you do.

2295
02:32:47,290 --> 02:32:52,000
That would punch a hole before the Stranger
ship could turn away as they do now."

2296
02:32:52,000 --> 02:32:53,000
Kendall nodded.

2297
02:32:53,000 --> 02:32:55,020
"That's what I was after.

2298
02:32:55,020 --> 02:32:56,850
It is mainly for the forts, though.

2299
02:32:56,850 --> 02:33:00,750
We'll have to signal the dope to the Mars
Center and Deenmor stations.

2300
02:33:00,750 --> 02:33:02,850
They can fix it up, themselves.

2301
02:33:02,850 --> 02:33:08,650
In the meantime—all we can do is hold on
and hunt, and let's hope better than the Strangers

2302
02:33:08,650 --> 02:33:14,800
do."

2303
02:33:14,800 --> 02:33:29,960
X
Sadly the convalescent Gresth Gkae listened

2304
02:33:29,960 --> 02:33:32,820
to the reports of his lieutenants.

2305
02:33:32,820 --> 02:33:37,970
More and more disgraced he felt as he realized
how badly he had blundered in reporting the

2306
02:33:37,970 --> 02:33:41,770
people of this system unable to cope with
the attackers' weapons.

2307
02:33:41,770 --> 02:33:47,180
Gresth Gkae looked up at his old friend and
physician, Merth Skahl.

2308
02:33:47,180 --> 02:33:48,950
He shook his head slowly.

2309
02:33:48,950 --> 02:33:50,109
"I'm afraid, Merth Skahl.

2310
02:33:50,109 --> 02:33:54,069
I am afraid.

2311
02:33:54,069 --> 02:33:56,649
We have, perhaps, made a mistake.

2312
02:33:56,649 --> 02:33:59,310
The better and the stronger alone should rule.

2313
02:33:59,310 --> 02:34:03,200
Aye, but is the stronger always the better?

2314
02:34:03,200 --> 02:34:06,990
I am afraid we have mistaken the Truth in
assuming this.

2315
02:34:06,990 --> 02:34:12,540
If we have—then may Jarth, Lord of Truth
and Wisdom punish us.

2316
02:34:12,540 --> 02:34:17,989
Mighty Jarth, if I have mistaken in following
my judgments, it is not from disobedience,

2317
02:34:17,989 --> 02:34:20,270
it is lack of Thy knowledge.

2318
02:34:20,270 --> 02:34:24,820
The strongest—they are not always the better,
are they?"

2319
02:34:24,820 --> 02:34:28,170
Merth Skahl bent sharply over his friend.

2320
02:34:28,170 --> 02:34:30,990
"Quiet thyself, Gresth Gkae.

2321
02:34:30,990 --> 02:34:36,880
You know, and I know, you have done only your
best, and surely Jarth himself can ask no

2322
02:34:36,880 --> 02:34:38,970
better of any one.

2323
02:34:38,970 --> 02:34:43,440
You must rest, for only by rest can those
terrible burns be healed.

2324
02:34:43,440 --> 02:34:48,280
All your stheen over half the body-area was
burned off.

2325
02:34:48,280 --> 02:34:50,779
You have been delirious for many days."

2326
02:34:50,779 --> 02:34:55,810
"But Merth Skahl, think—have we disobeyed
Jarth's will?

2327
02:34:55,810 --> 02:35:01,510
It is, we know, his will that only the best
and the strongest shall rule—but are the

2328
02:35:01,510 --> 02:35:03,850
best always the strongest?

2329
02:35:03,850 --> 02:35:08,280
An imbecile adult could destroy the life of
a genius-grade child.

2330
02:35:08,280 --> 02:35:13,101
The strongest wins, but not the best.

2331
02:35:13,101 --> 02:35:15,900
Such would not be the will of Jarth.

2332
02:35:15,900 --> 02:35:21,170
If we be the stronger, and the best, then
it is right and just that these strange creatures

2333
02:35:21,170 --> 02:35:25,569
should be destroyed that we may have a stable
world of stable light and heat.

2334
02:35:25,569 --> 02:35:30,930
But look and see, with what terrible swiftness
these strange creatures have learned!

2335
02:35:30,930 --> 02:35:37,700
May it not be they are the better race—that
it is we who are the weaker and the poorer?

2336
02:35:37,700 --> 02:35:42,780
Can it be that Jarth has brought us together
that these people might learn—and destroy

2337
02:35:42,780 --> 02:35:44,300
us?

2338
02:35:44,300 --> 02:35:49,680
If they be the stronger, and the better—then
may Jarth's will be done.

2339
02:35:49,680 --> 02:35:52,300
But we must test our strength to the utmost.

2340
02:35:52,300 --> 02:35:55,700
I must rise, and go to my laboratory soon.

2341
02:35:55,700 --> 02:35:57,649
They have set it up?"

2342
02:35:57,649 --> 02:35:59,700
"Aye, they have, Gresth Gkae.

2343
02:35:59,700 --> 02:36:05,380
But remember, the weak and the sick make faults
the strong and the well do not.

2344
02:36:05,380 --> 02:36:07,310
Better that you rest yourself.

2345
02:36:07,310 --> 02:36:12,290
There is little you can do while your body
seeks to recover from these terrible burns."

2346
02:36:12,290 --> 02:36:15,439
"You are wrong, my friend, wrong.

2347
02:36:15,439 --> 02:36:22,810
Don't you see that my mind is clear—that
it is the mind which must fight in these battles,

2348
02:36:22,810 --> 02:36:26,750
for surely the man is weak against such things
as this infra-X-radiation?

2349
02:36:26,750 --> 02:36:33,101
Why, I am better able to fight now than are
you, for I am a trained fighter of the mind,

2350
02:36:33,101 --> 02:36:36,439
while you are a trained healer of the body.

2351
02:36:36,439 --> 02:36:41,980
These strange beings with their stiff arms
and legs, their tender skins, and—and their

2352
02:36:41,980 --> 02:36:45,660
swift minds have fought us all too well.

2353
02:36:45,660 --> 02:36:48,989
If we must test, let it be a test.

2354
02:36:48,989 --> 02:36:52,609
I have heard how they so quickly solved the
riddle of the crumbling field.

2355
02:36:52,609 --> 02:36:56,020
That took us longer, and we designed it.

2356
02:36:56,020 --> 02:37:01,550
The Counsel of Worlds put me in command, let
me up, Skahl, I must work."

2357
02:37:01,550 --> 02:37:04,939
Concerned, the physician looked down at him.

2358
02:37:04,939 --> 02:37:07,160
Finally he spoke again.

2359
02:37:07,160 --> 02:37:11,399
"No, I will not permit you to leave the hospital-ship.

2360
02:37:11,399 --> 02:37:17,860
You must stay here, but if, as you have said,
the mind is what must fight, then surely you

2361
02:37:17,860 --> 02:37:20,529
can fight well from here, for your mind is
here."

2362
02:37:20,529 --> 02:37:23,930
"No, I cannot, and you well know it.

2363
02:37:23,930 --> 02:37:27,109
I may shorten my life, but what matter.

2364
02:37:27,109 --> 02:37:32,640
'Death is the end toward which the chemical
reaction, Life, tends,'" quoted the scientist.

2365
02:37:32,640 --> 02:37:37,290
"You know I have left my children—my immortality
is assured through them.

2366
02:37:37,290 --> 02:37:41,720
I can afford to die in peace, if it assures
their welfare.

2367
02:37:41,720 --> 02:37:48,620
Time is precious, and while my mind might
work from here, it must have data on which

2368
02:37:48,620 --> 02:37:49,620
to work.

2369
02:37:49,620 --> 02:37:52,890
For that, I must go to the laboratories.

2370
02:37:52,890 --> 02:37:56,950
Help me, Merth Skahl."

2371
02:37:56,950 --> 02:38:02,890
Reluctantly the physician granted the request,
but begged of Gresth Gkae a promise of at

2372
02:38:02,890 --> 02:38:08,021
least six hours rest in every fifteen, and
a good sleep of at least twenty-seven hours

2373
02:38:08,021 --> 02:38:10,189
every "night."

2374
02:38:10,189 --> 02:38:16,660
Gresth Gkae agreed, and from a wheelchair,
conducted his work, began a new line of experimentation

2375
02:38:16,660 --> 02:38:20,010
he hoped would yield them the weapon they
needed.

2376
02:38:20,010 --> 02:38:25,960
Under him, the staff of scientists worked,
aiding and advising and suggesting.

2377
02:38:25,960 --> 02:38:30,590
The apparatus was built, tested, and found
wanting.

2378
02:38:30,590 --> 02:38:36,740
Time and again as the days passed, they watched
Gresth Gkae, gaining strength very, very slowly,

2379
02:38:36,740 --> 02:38:41,460
taken away despondent at the end of his forty
hours of work.

2380
02:38:41,460 --> 02:38:47,260
A dozen expeditions were sent to Jupiter's
poles to watch and measure and study the tremendous

2381
02:38:47,260 --> 02:38:53,890
auroral displays there, where Jupiter's vast
magnetic field sucked in countless quintillions

2382
02:38:53,890 --> 02:38:59,521
of the flying electrons from the sun, and
brought them circling in, in a vast, magnificent

2383
02:38:59,521 --> 02:39:04,250
display of auroral ionization.

2384
02:39:04,250 --> 02:39:09,020
Expeditions went to the great Southern Plateau,
the Plateau of Storms, where the titanic air

2385
02:39:09,020 --> 02:39:14,510
currents resulted in an everlasting display
