2653
02:58:28,871 --> 02:58:30,620
have the system.

2654
02:58:30,620 --> 02:58:31,880
This was the home planet.

2655
02:58:31,880 --> 02:58:37,720
If this fell, then the two others would follow
easily, despite the fact that the few forts

2656
02:58:37,720 --> 02:58:42,560
on the innermost planet, Mercury, could gather
energy from the sun at a rate greater than

2657
02:58:42,560 --> 02:58:44,529
their ships could generate.

2658
02:58:44,529 --> 02:58:49,720
It took Kendall two weeks and three days to
set up his preliminary apparatus.

2659
02:58:49,720 --> 02:58:55,150
They had power for perhaps four days more,
thanks to the fact that the long Lunar day

2660
02:58:55,150 --> 02:59:00,050
had begun shortly after Gresth Gkae's impatient
attack had started.

2661
02:59:00,050 --> 02:59:06,430
Also, the "S Doradus" had brought in several
hundred tons of charged mercury on each trip,

2662
02:59:06,430 --> 02:59:11,899
though this was no great quantity individually,
it had mounted up in the ten trips she had

2663
02:59:11,899 --> 02:59:13,239
made.

2664
02:59:13,239 --> 02:59:19,460
The "Cepheid," her sister ship, had gone along
on seven of the trips, and added to the total.

2665
02:59:19,460 --> 02:59:22,360
But at length the apparatus was set up.

2666
02:59:22,360 --> 02:59:27,940
It was peculiar looking, and it employed a
great deal of power, nearly as much as a UV

2667
02:59:27,940 --> 02:59:29,370
beam in fact.

2668
02:59:29,370 --> 02:59:35,210
McLaurin looked at it sceptically toward the
last, and asked Buck: "What do you expect

2669
02:59:35,210 --> 02:59:36,689
it to do?"

2670
02:59:36,689 --> 02:59:42,270
"I am," said Kendall sourly, "uncertain.

2671
02:59:42,270 --> 02:59:45,170
The result will be uncertainty itself."

2672
02:59:45,170 --> 02:59:51,530
Which, considering things, was a surprisingly
accurate statement.

2673
02:59:51,530 --> 02:59:53,630
Kendall gave the exact answer.

2674
02:59:53,630 --> 02:59:56,699
He meant to give an ironic comment.

2675
02:59:56,699 --> 03:00:03,319
For the mathematics had been perfectly correct,
only Buck Kendall misinterpreted the answer.

2676
03:00:03,319 --> 03:00:08,910
"I've followed the math with mechanism all
the way through," he explained, "and I'm putting

2677
03:00:08,910 --> 03:00:10,170
power into it.

2678
03:00:10,170 --> 03:00:11,390
That's all I know.

2679
03:00:11,390 --> 03:00:17,470
Somewhere, by the laws of cause and effect,
this power must show itself again—despite

2680
03:00:17,470 --> 03:00:20,310
what the damn math says."

2681
03:00:20,310 --> 03:00:22,149
And in that, of course, Kendall was wrong.

2682
03:00:22,149 --> 03:00:27,570
Because the laws of cause and effect didn't
hold in what he was doing now.

2683
03:00:27,570 --> 03:00:30,529
"Do you want to watch?" he asked at length.

2684
03:00:30,529 --> 03:00:32,430
"I'm all set to try it."

2685
03:00:32,430 --> 03:00:34,609
"I suppose I may as well."

2686
03:00:34,609 --> 03:00:35,770
McLaurin smiled.

2687
03:00:35,770 --> 03:00:40,149
"In our close-knit little community the fate
of one is of interest to all.

2688
03:00:40,149 --> 03:00:46,489
If it's going to blow up, I might as well
be here, and if it isn't, I want to be."

2689
03:00:46,489 --> 03:00:51,380
Kendall smiled appreciatively and replied:
"Let it be on thy own head.

2690
03:00:51,380 --> 03:00:52,689
Here she goes."

2691
03:00:52,689 --> 03:00:56,470
He walked over to the power board, and took
command.

2692
03:00:56,470 --> 03:01:01,380
Devin, and a squad of other scientists were
seated about the room with every conceivable

2693
03:01:01,380 --> 03:01:03,820
type and combination of apparatus.

2694
03:01:03,820 --> 03:01:06,800
Kendall wanted to see what this was doing.

2695
03:01:06,800 --> 03:01:08,420
"Tubes," he called.

2696
03:01:08,420 --> 03:01:11,040
"Circuits A and D. Tie-ins."

2697
03:01:11,040 --> 03:01:14,340
He stopped, the preliminary switches in.

2698
03:01:14,340 --> 03:01:16,920
"Main circuit coming."

2699
03:01:16,920 --> 03:01:20,569
With a jerk he threw over the last contact.

2700
03:01:20,569 --> 03:01:23,550
A heavy relay thudded solidly.

2701
03:01:23,550 --> 03:01:25,990
The hum of a straining atostor.

2702
03:01:25,990 --> 03:01:27,319
Then—

2703
03:01:27,319 --> 03:01:31,800
An electric motor, humming smoothly stopped
with a jerk.

2704
03:01:31,800 --> 03:01:42,479
"This," it remarked in a deep throaty voice,
"is probably the last stand of humanity."

2705
03:01:42,479 --> 03:01:46,600
The galvanometer before which Devin was seated
apparently agreed.

2706
03:01:46,600 --> 03:01:52,859
In a rather high pitched voice it pointed
out that: "If the Lunar Fort falls, the Earth—"

2707
03:01:52,859 --> 03:01:58,930
It stopped abruptly, and an electroscope beside
Douglass took up the thread in a high, shrill

2708
03:01:58,930 --> 03:02:02,800
voice, rather slurred, "—will be directly
attacked."

2709
03:02:02,800 --> 03:02:11,449
"This," resumed the motor in a hoarse voice,
"will certainly mean the end of humanity."

2710
03:02:11,449 --> 03:02:17,029
The motor gave up the discourse and hummed
violently into action—in reverse!

2711
03:02:17,029 --> 03:02:19,600
"My God!"

2712
03:02:19,600 --> 03:02:23,640
Kendall pulled the switch open with a sagging
jaw and staring eyes.

2713
03:02:23,640 --> 03:02:29,700
The men in the room burst into sudden startled
exclamations.

2714
03:02:29,700 --> 03:02:31,470
Kendall didn't give them time.

2715
03:02:31,470 --> 03:02:37,820
His jaw snapped shut, and a blazing light
of wondrous joy shone in his eyes.

2716
03:02:37,820 --> 03:02:41,410
He instantly threw the switch in again.

2717
03:02:41,410 --> 03:02:46,210
Again the humming atostor, the strain—

2718
03:02:46,210 --> 03:02:48,170
Slowly Devin lifted from his seat.

2719
03:02:48,170 --> 03:02:55,439
With thrashing arms and startled, staring
eyes, he drifted gently across the room.

2720
03:02:55,439 --> 03:02:59,410
Abruptly he fell to the floor, unhurt by the
light Lunar gravity.

2721
03:02:59,410 --> 03:03:08,550
"I advise," said the motor in its grumbling
voice, "an immediate exodus."

2722
03:03:08,550 --> 03:03:12,560
It stopped speaking, and practiced what it
preached.

2723
03:03:12,560 --> 03:03:19,330
It was a fifty-horse motor-generator, on a
five-ton tungsten-beryllium base, but it rose

2724
03:03:19,330 --> 03:03:25,850
abruptly, spun rapidly about an axis at right
angles to the axis of its armature, and stopped

2725
03:03:25,850 --> 03:03:27,739
as suddenly.

2726
03:03:27,739 --> 03:03:31,660
In mid air it continued its interrupted lecture.

2727
03:03:31,660 --> 03:03:36,000
"Mercury therefore is the destination I would
advise.

2728
03:03:36,000 --> 03:03:42,220
There power is sufficient for—all machines."

2729
03:03:42,220 --> 03:03:47,140
Gently it inverted itself and settled to the
middle of the floor.

2730
03:03:47,140 --> 03:03:49,040
Kendall instantly cut the switch.

2731
03:03:49,040 --> 03:03:51,850
The relay did not chunk open.

2732
03:03:51,850 --> 03:03:54,790
It refused to obey.

2733
03:03:54,790 --> 03:04:00,439
Settled in the middle of the floor now, torn
loose from its power leads, the motor-generator

2734
03:04:00,439 --> 03:04:01,790
began turning.

2735
03:04:01,790 --> 03:04:04,979
It turned faster and faster.

2736
03:04:04,979 --> 03:04:11,149
It was shrilling in a thin scream of terrific
speed, a speed that should have torn its windings

2737
03:04:11,149 --> 03:04:15,290
to fragments under the lash of centrifugal
force.

2738
03:04:15,290 --> 03:04:16,771
Contentedly it said throatily.

2739
03:04:16,771 --> 03:04:17,771
"Settled."

2740
03:04:17,771 --> 03:04:25,060
The galvanometer spoke again in its peculiar
harsh voice.

2741
03:04:25,060 --> 03:04:27,319
"Therefore, move."

2742
03:04:27,319 --> 03:04:32,120
Abruptly, without apparent reason, the stubborn
relay clicked open.

2743
03:04:32,120 --> 03:04:39,310
The shrilly screaming motor stopped dead instantly,
as though it had had no real momentum, or

2744
03:04:39,310 --> 03:04:41,239
had been inertialess.

2745
03:04:41,239 --> 03:04:45,220
Startled, white-faced men looked at Kendall.

2746
03:04:45,220 --> 03:04:49,490
Buck's eyes were shining with an unholy glee.

2747
03:04:49,490 --> 03:04:51,279
"Uncertainty!"

2748
03:04:51,279 --> 03:04:53,359
he shouted.

2749
03:04:53,359 --> 03:04:56,060
"Uncertainty—uncertainty—uncertainty,
you fools!

2750
03:04:56,060 --> 03:04:57,149
Don't you see it?

2751
03:04:57,149 --> 03:05:04,520
All the math—it said uncertainty—man,
man—we've got just that—uncertainty!"

2752
03:05:04,520 --> 03:05:07,779
"You're crazy," gasped McLaurin.

2753
03:05:07,779 --> 03:05:12,819
"I'm crazy, everything's gone crazy."

2754
03:05:12,819 --> 03:05:16,420
Kendall roared with sudden, joyous laughter.

2755
03:05:16,420 --> 03:05:17,420
"Absolutely.

2756
03:05:17,420 --> 03:05:21,939
Everything goes crazy—the laws of nature
break down!

2757
03:05:21,939 --> 03:05:27,410
Heisenberg's principle showed that the law
of cause and effect weren't absolute.

2758
03:05:27,410 --> 03:05:30,810
We've made them absolutely uncertain!"

2759
03:05:30,810 --> 03:05:36,430
"But—but motors talking, instruments giving
lectures—"

2760
03:05:36,430 --> 03:05:42,300
"Certainly—or rather uncertainly—anything,
absolutely anything.

2761
03:05:42,300 --> 03:05:48,190
The destruction of the laws of gravity, freedom
from inertia—why, merely picking up a radio

2762
03:05:48,190 --> 03:05:50,290
lecture is nothing!"

2763
03:05:50,290 --> 03:05:55,279
Suddenly, abruptly, a thousand questions poured
in on him.

2764
03:05:55,279 --> 03:06:00,790
Jubilantly he answered what he could, told
what he thought—and then brought order.

2765
03:06:00,790 --> 03:06:05,790
"The battle's still on, men—we've still
got to find out how to use this, now we've

2766
03:06:05,790 --> 03:06:06,790
got it.

2767
03:06:06,790 --> 03:06:09,729
I have an idea—that there's a lot more.

2768
03:06:09,729 --> 03:06:12,020
I know what I'll get this time.

2769
03:06:12,020 --> 03:06:16,189
Now help me remake this apparatus so we don't
broadcast the thing."

2770
03:06:16,189 --> 03:06:21,890
At once, ten times the former pace, work was
done.

2771
03:06:21,890 --> 03:06:26,270
On the radio, news was sent out that Kendall
was on the right track after all.

2772
03:06:26,270 --> 03:06:32,850
In two hours the apparatus had been vastly
altered, it was in the final stage, and an

2773
03:06:32,850 --> 03:06:34,920
entirely different sort of field set up.

2774
03:06:34,920 --> 03:06:38,989
Again they watched as Buck applied the power.

2775
03:06:38,989 --> 03:06:44,779
The atostor hummed—but no strange tricks
of matter happened this time.

2776
03:06:44,779 --> 03:06:50,180
The more concentrated, altered field was,
as Buck was to find out later, "Uncertainty

2777
03:06:50,180 --> 03:06:51,680
of the Second Degree."

2778
03:06:51,680 --> 03:06:55,340
It was molecular uncertainty.

2779
03:06:55,340 --> 03:07:00,721
In a field a foot and a half in diameter,
Buck saw the thing created—and suddenly

2780
03:07:00,721 --> 03:07:07,130
a brilliant green-blue flame shot up, and
a great dark cloud of terrible, red-brown

2781
03:07:07,130 --> 03:07:08,130
deadly vapor.

2782
03:07:08,130 --> 03:07:11,920
Then an instant later, Kendall had opened
the relay.

2783
03:07:11,920 --> 03:07:16,021
Gasping, the men ran from the laboratory,
shutting the deadly fumes in.

2784
03:07:16,021 --> 03:07:21,229
"N2O4" gasped Morton, the chemist, as they
reached safety.

2785
03:07:21,229 --> 03:07:24,149
"It's exothermic—but it formed there!"

2786
03:07:24,149 --> 03:07:30,760
In that instant, Kendall grasped the meaning
the choking fumes carried.

2787
03:07:30,760 --> 03:07:33,950
"Molecular uncertainty!" he decided.

2788
03:07:33,950 --> 03:07:37,670
"We're going back—we're getting there—"

2789
03:07:37,670 --> 03:07:43,870
He altered the apparatus again, added another
atostor in series, reduced the size of his

2790
03:07:43,870 --> 03:07:47,930
sphere of forces—of strange chaos of uncertainty.

2791
03:07:47,930 --> 03:07:50,770
Within—little was certain.

2792
03:07:50,770 --> 03:07:54,570
Without—the laws of nature applied as ever.

2793
03:07:54,570 --> 03:07:59,189
Again the apparatus was started, cautiously
this time.

2794
03:07:59,189 --> 03:08:05,069
Only a strange jumbled ionization appeared
this time, then a slow, rising blue flame

2795
03:08:05,069 --> 03:08:09,310
began to creep up, and burn hot and blue.

2796
03:08:09,310 --> 03:08:15,090
Buck looked at it for a moment, then his face
grew tense and thoughtful.

2797
03:08:15,090 --> 03:08:16,090
"Devin—give me a half-dollar."

2798
03:08:16,090 --> 03:08:22,000
Blankly, Devin reached in his pocket, and
handed over the metal disc.

2799
03:08:22,000 --> 03:08:26,199
Cautiously Buck Kendall tossed it toward the
sphere of force.

2800
03:08:26,199 --> 03:08:28,980
Instantly there was a flash of flame, soundless
and soft-colored.

2801
03:08:28,980 --> 03:08:36,510
Then the silver disc was outlined in light,
and swiftly, inevitably crumbling into dust

2802
03:08:36,510 --> 03:08:40,449
so fine only a blue haze appeared.

2803
03:08:40,449 --> 03:08:43,771
In less than two seconds, the metal was gone.

2804
03:08:43,771 --> 03:08:46,620
Only the dense blue fog remained.

2805
03:08:46,620 --> 03:08:51,740
Then this began to go, and the leaping blue
flame grew taller, and stronger.

2806
03:08:51,740 --> 03:08:55,609
"We're on the track—I'm going to stop here,
and calculate.

2807
03:08:55,609 --> 03:08:57,449
Bring the data—"

2808
03:08:57,449 --> 03:09:01,180
Kendall shut off the machine, and went to
the calculation room.

2809
03:09:01,180 --> 03:09:05,710
Swiftly he selected already prepared graphs,
graphs of the math he had worked on.

2810
03:09:05,710 --> 03:09:08,100
Devin came soon, and others.

2811
03:09:08,100 --> 03:09:13,910
They assembled the data and with tables and
arithmetical machines turned it into graphs.

2812
03:09:13,910 --> 03:09:16,660
Then all these graphs were fed into the machine.

2813
03:09:16,660 --> 03:09:21,880
There were curves, and sine-curves, abrupt
breaking lines—but the answer that came

2814
03:09:21,880 --> 03:09:27,739
when all were compounded was a perfect diagram
of a flight of four steps, descending in unequal

2815
03:09:27,739 --> 03:09:31,260
treads to zero.

2816
03:09:31,260 --> 03:09:33,529
Kendall looked at it for long minutes.

2817
03:09:33,529 --> 03:09:37,510
"That," he said at length, "is what I expected.

2818
03:09:37,510 --> 03:09:43,530
There are four degrees of uncertainty, we
generated 'Uncertainty of the First Degree,'

2819
03:09:43,530 --> 03:09:46,050
'Mass Uncertainty,' when we started.

2820
03:09:46,050 --> 03:09:49,260
That, as here shown, takes little energy concentration.

2821
03:09:49,260 --> 03:09:54,840
Then we increased the energy concentration
and got 'Uncertainty of the Second Degree,'

2822
03:09:54,840 --> 03:09:55,949
'Molecular Uncertainty.'

2823
03:09:55,949 --> 03:10:03,000
Then I added more power, and reduced the field,
and got 'Uncertainty of the Third Degree'—'Atomic

2824
03:10:03,000 --> 03:10:04,790
Uncertainty.'

2825
03:10:04,790 --> 03:10:07,529
There is 'Uncertainty of the Fourth Degree.'

2826
03:10:07,529 --> 03:10:10,750
It is barely attainable with our atostors.

2827
03:10:10,750 --> 03:10:13,070
It is—utter uncertainty.

2828
03:10:13,070 --> 03:10:20,351
"In the First Degree, the laws of mass action
fail, the great broad-reaching laws.

2829
03:10:20,351 --> 03:10:25,609
In the Second Degree, the laws of the molecules,
a finer organization, break down, and anything

2830
03:10:25,609 --> 03:10:28,220
can happen in chemistry.

2831
03:10:28,220 --> 03:10:32,409
In the Third Degree, the laws of atomic physics
break down slowly.

2832
03:10:32,409 --> 03:10:33,420
The atom is tough.

2833
03:10:33,420 --> 03:10:39,970
It is very compact, and we just barely attained
the concentration needed with that apparatus.

2834
03:10:39,970 --> 03:10:46,430
But—in the Third Degree, when the Atomic
Laws break down into utter uncertainty, the

2835
03:10:46,430 --> 03:10:50,050
atoms break, and only hydrogen can exist.

2836
03:10:50,050 --> 03:10:51,659
That was the blue flame.

2837
03:10:51,659 --> 03:11:01,159
"But the Fourth Degree—there is no law whatsoever,
nothing in all the Universe can exist.

2838
03:11:01,159 --> 03:11:07,040
It means—the utter destruction and release
of the energy of matter!"

2839
03:11:07,040 --> 03:11:08,850
Kendall paused for a moment.

2840
03:11:08,850 --> 03:11:11,609
"We have won, with this.

2841
03:11:11,609 --> 03:11:17,090
We need only make up this apparatus—and
maybe make it into a weapon.

2842
03:11:17,090 --> 03:11:22,210
You know, in the Fourth Degree, nothing in
all the Universe could resist, deflect, or

2843
03:11:22,210 --> 03:11:25,030
control it, if launched freely, and self-maintaining.

2844
03:11:25,030 --> 03:11:27,760
I think that might be done.

2845
03:11:27,760 --> 03:11:33,050
You see, no law affects it, for it breaks
down the law.

2846
03:11:33,050 --> 03:11:38,000
Magnetism cannot attract or repel it because
magnetic fields cannot exist; there is no

2847
03:11:38,000 --> 03:11:41,090
law of magnetic force, where this field is.

2848
03:11:41,090 --> 03:11:46,800
"And you know, Devin, how I have analyzed
and duplicated their magnetic ball-fields.

2849
03:11:46,800 --> 03:11:49,650
This should be capable of formation into a
ball-field.

2850
03:11:49,650 --> 03:11:53,410
"We need only make it up now.

2851
03:11:53,410 --> 03:11:58,739
We will install it in the 'S Doradus' and
the 'Cepheid' as a weapon.

2852
03:11:58,739 --> 03:12:05,680
We need only install it as an energy source
here.

2853
03:12:05,680 --> 03:12:19,260
Let us start."

2854
03:12:19,260 --> 03:12:26,410
XII
Buck Kendall with a slow smile, looked out

2855
03:12:26,410 --> 03:12:29,100
of the port in the thick metal wall.

2856
03:12:29,100 --> 03:12:34,949
The magnetic shield of the Lunar Fort was
washed constantly with the fires of exploding

2857
03:12:34,949 --> 03:12:37,080
magnetic bombs.

2858
03:12:37,080 --> 03:12:39,029
The smile spread broader.

2859
03:12:39,029 --> 03:12:47,319
"My friends," he said softly, "you can pull
from now till doomsday as far as I'm concerned,

2860
03:12:47,319 --> 03:12:51,050
and you won't even disturb us now."

2861
03:12:51,050 --> 03:12:54,090
He looked back over his shoulder into the
power room.

2862
03:12:54,090 --> 03:12:59,670
A hunched bulk, beautifully designed and carefully
finished, the apparatus that created 'Uncertainty

2863
03:12:59,670 --> 03:13:06,330
of the Fourth Degree' was destroying matter,
and creating by its destruction terrific electric

2864
03:13:06,330 --> 03:13:07,330
fields.

2865
03:13:07,330 --> 03:13:10,840
These fields were feeding the magnetic shield
now.

2866
03:13:10,840 --> 03:13:14,170
Under the present drain, the machine was not
noticeably working.

2867
03:13:14,170 --> 03:13:17,280
In fact, Kendall was a bit annoyed.

2868
03:13:17,280 --> 03:13:22,870
He had tested out the energy generating properties
of this machine, trying to find a limit.

2869
03:13:22,870 --> 03:13:25,439
He had found there was no limit.

2870
03:13:25,439 --> 03:13:30,529
The great copper conductors, charged with
the same atostor force that was used in the

2871
03:13:30,529 --> 03:13:34,870
mercury fuel, were perfect conductors, they
had not heated.

2872
03:13:34,870 --> 03:13:39,479
But the eleven thousand tons of discharged
mercury metal had been completely charged

2873
03:13:39,479 --> 03:13:43,390
in just a bit better than eleven minutes.

2874
03:13:43,390 --> 03:13:48,520
The pumps wouldn't force it through the charging
apparatus any faster than that.

2875
03:13:48,520 --> 03:13:53,640
Two weeks more had passed, while the "S Doradus"
and the "Cepheid" were fitted out with the

2876
03:13:53,640 --> 03:13:55,960
new apparatus Buck had designed.

2877
03:13:55,960 --> 03:13:59,870
They were almost ready to start now.

2878
03:13:59,870 --> 03:14:03,310
McLaurin came down the corridor, and stopped
near Kendall.

2879
03:14:03,310 --> 03:14:05,640
He too smiled at the Miran's attempts.

2880
03:14:05,640 --> 03:14:08,760
"They've got a long way to go, Buck."

2881
03:14:08,760 --> 03:14:11,310
"They're going a long way.

2882
03:14:11,310 --> 03:14:14,680
Clear back home—and we'll be right along.

2883
03:14:14,680 --> 03:14:17,270
I don't think they can outdistance us."

2884
03:14:17,270 --> 03:14:22,250
"I still don't see why you couldn't use one
of those Uncertainty conditions—the First

2885
03:14:22,250 --> 03:14:24,400
Degree perhaps, and annihilate our inertia."

2886
03:14:24,400 --> 03:14:28,270
"You can't control Uncertainty.

2887
03:14:28,270 --> 03:14:31,580
By its essential character it's beyond control."

2888
03:14:31,580 --> 03:14:37,021
"What's that Fourth Degree machine of yours—the
material energy—if it isn't controlled and

2889
03:14:37,021 --> 03:14:39,010
utilized Uncertainty?"

2890
03:14:39,010 --> 03:14:42,479
"It's utter and utterly uncontrolled Uncertainty.

2891
03:14:42,479 --> 03:14:47,040
The matter within that field breaks down to
absolutely nothing.

2892
03:14:47,040 --> 03:14:54,840
Within, no law whatsoever applies, but fortunately,
outside the old laws of physics apply—and

2893
03:14:54,840 --> 03:14:59,689
we can gather and use the energy which is
released outside, though nothing can be done

2894
03:14:59,689 --> 03:15:00,689
inside.

2895
03:15:00,689 --> 03:15:07,830
Why, think, man, if I could control that Uncertainty,
I could do anything at all, absolutely anything.

2896
03:15:07,830 --> 03:15:12,540
It would be a world as unreasonable as a bad
dream.

2897
03:15:12,540 --> 03:15:17,029
Think how unreasonable those manifestations
we first got were!"

2898
03:15:17,029 --> 03:15:20,870
"But can't you get any control at all?"

2899
03:15:20,870 --> 03:15:22,350
"Very little.

2900
03:15:22,350 --> 03:15:27,189
Anyway, if I could get inertialess conditions
at will, I'd be afraid of them.

2901
03:15:27,189 --> 03:15:32,540
They'd make chemical reactions impossible
in all probability—and life is chemical.

2902
03:15:32,540 --> 03:15:38,390
Two atoms must come into more or less violent
contact before a union takes place, and cannot

2903
03:15:38,390 --> 03:15:40,960
if they have neither momentum nor inertia.

2904
03:15:40,960 --> 03:15:43,020
"Anyway—why worry.

2905
03:15:43,020 --> 03:15:46,080
I can't do it, because I can't control this
thing.

2906
03:15:46,080 --> 03:15:48,530
And we have the extra-space drive."

2907
03:15:48,530 --> 03:15:51,870
"How does that darned thing work?

2908
03:15:51,870 --> 03:15:55,040
Can't you drop the math and tell me about
it?"

2909
03:15:55,040 --> 03:15:56,040
Kendall smiled.

2910
03:15:56,040 --> 03:15:57,920
"Not too readily.

2911
03:15:57,920 --> 03:16:03,100
Remember first, as to the driving system,
that it works on the fabric of space.

2912
03:16:03,100 --> 03:16:09,120
Space is, in the physical sense, a fabric
woven of the threads of lines of force from

2913
03:16:09,120 --> 03:16:13,279
every body in the universe, made up of fields
and forces.

2914
03:16:13,279 --> 03:16:17,640
It is elastic, and can transmit strains.

2915
03:16:17,640 --> 03:16:22,010
But anything that can transmit strains, can
be strained against.

2916
03:16:22,010 --> 03:16:28,020
With the tremendous field intensities available
by the material engines, I can get such fields

2917
03:16:28,020 --> 03:16:31,229
as will 'dig their toes' into space and push.

2918
03:16:31,229 --> 03:16:34,140
"That's the drive itself.

2919
03:16:34,140 --> 03:16:39,360
It is accelerationless, because it enfolds
us, and acts equally on every atom of us.

2920
03:16:39,360 --> 03:16:45,029
By maintaining in addition a slight artificial
gravity—thanks also to the intensity of

2921
03:16:45,029 --> 03:16:51,340
those material engine fields—we can be comfortable,
while we accelerate at tremendous rates.

2922
03:16:51,340 --> 03:16:56,189
"That is, I think, at least allied to the
Stranger's system.

2923
03:16:56,189 --> 03:17:01,020
For the high-speed drive, I do in fact use
the Uncertainty.

2924
03:17:01,020 --> 03:17:07,300
I can control it in a certain sense by determining
its powers, and the limits of uncertainty,

2925
03:17:07,300 --> 03:17:09,910
whether First, Second, Third or Fourth Degree.

2926
03:17:09,910 --> 03:17:16,560
It advances in jumps—but on a finer plotting
of the curve, you can see that each jump represents

2927
03:17:16,560 --> 03:17:19,229
a vast series of smaller jumps.

2928
03:17:19,229 --> 03:17:24,699
That is, there is Class A, B, C, D, and so
forth Uncertainty of the First Degree.

2929
03:17:24,699 --> 03:17:30,760
Now Class A First Degree Uncertainty involves
only the deepest, broadest principles.

2930
03:17:30,760 --> 03:17:32,949
Only they break down.

2931
03:17:32,949 --> 03:17:36,040
One of these is the law of the speed of light.

2932
03:17:36,040 --> 03:17:40,659
"I'm sure that isn't the system the Strangers
use, but I'm also sure there's no limit to

2933
03:17:40,659 --> 03:17:42,380
the speed we can get."

2934
03:17:42,380 --> 03:17:45,439
"Doesn't that wreck your drive system?"

2935
03:17:45,439 --> 03:17:50,540
"No, because gravity and the fields I use
in driving are First Degree Uncertainties

2936
03:17:50,540 --> 03:17:51,680
of the higher classes.

2937
03:17:51,680 --> 03:17:54,550
"But at any rate, it will work.

2938
03:17:54,550 --> 03:17:57,239
And—I suspect you came to say you were ready
to go."

2939
03:17:57,239 --> 03:17:58,760
"I did."

2940
03:17:58,760 --> 03:18:00,290
McLaurin nodded.

2941
03:18:00,290 --> 03:18:02,790
"Still stick to your original plan?"

2942
03:18:02,790 --> 03:18:04,130
McLaurin nodded.

2943
03:18:04,130 --> 03:18:06,370
"I think it's best.

2944
03:18:06,370 --> 03:18:10,880
You follow those fellows back to their system
in the 'S Doradus' and I'll stay here in the

2945
03:18:10,880 --> 03:18:12,600
'Cepheid' to protect the system.

2946
03:18:12,600 --> 03:18:15,430
They may need some time to get out of the
place here.

2947
03:18:15,430 --> 03:18:19,090
And remember, we ought to be as decent as
they were.

2948
03:18:19,090 --> 03:18:23,620
They didn't bother the transports leaving
Jupiter when they came in, only attacked the

2949
03:18:23,620 --> 03:18:24,620
warships.

2950
03:18:24,620 --> 03:18:29,529
We're bound to do the same, but we'll have
to keep a watch on them, nonetheless.

2951
03:18:29,529 --> 03:18:31,540
So you go on ahead."

2952
03:18:31,540 --> 03:18:36,710
They started down the corridor, and came presently
to the huge locks where the "S Doradus" and

2953
03:18:36,710 --> 03:18:39,029
the "Cepheid" were berthed.

2954
03:18:39,029 --> 03:18:45,490
The super-ships lay cold and gray now, men
swarming in and out with last-minute supplies.

2955
03:18:45,490 --> 03:18:49,460
Air, water, spare parts, bedding and personal
equipment.

2956
03:18:49,460 --> 03:18:54,430
Douglass, Cole, and most of the laboratory
staff would go with Kendall when he followed

2957
03:18:54,430 --> 03:18:56,050
the Strangers home.

2958
03:18:56,050 --> 03:19:02,979
Devin and a few of the most advanced physicists
would stay with McLaurin in case of need.

2959
03:19:02,979 --> 03:19:09,130
An hour later the "S Doradus" rose gently,
soundlessly from her berth, and floated out

2960
03:19:09,130 --> 03:19:10,130
of the open lock-door.

2961
03:19:10,130 --> 03:19:14,930
The "Cepheid" followed her in five seconds.

2962
03:19:14,930 --> 03:19:20,150
Still under the great screen of the fort,
the lashing, coruscating colors of the magnetic

2963
03:19:20,150 --> 03:19:24,220
bombs and the magnetic screen flashed and
was iridescent.

2964
03:19:24,220 --> 03:19:29,550
The "S Doradus" poked her great nose gently
through the screen, and an instant later her

2965
03:19:29,550 --> 03:19:36,330
titanically powerful, material-engine effortlessly
discharged a great magnetic bomb, sent with

2966
03:19:36,330 --> 03:19:40,410
the combined power of five atomic-powered
interstellar ships.

2967
03:19:40,410 --> 03:19:46,580
The two ships separated now, the "Cepheid"
under McLaurin flashing ahead with sudden,

2968
03:19:46,580 --> 03:19:51,930
terrific acceleration toward Mars, whispering
through space at a speed that made it undetectable,

2969
03:19:51,930 --> 03:19:54,040
faster than light.

2970
03:19:54,040 --> 03:20:00,290
The "S Doradus" journeyed out leisurely toward
the fleet of forty-seven Miran ships.

2971
03:20:00,290 --> 03:20:06,100
Gresth Gkae saw the "S Doradus" and as he
watched the steady progress, felt sudden fear

2972
03:20:06,100 --> 03:20:07,779
at his heart.

2973
03:20:07,779 --> 03:20:11,239
The ship seemed so certain—

2974
03:20:11,239 --> 03:20:15,510
At a distance of thirty thousand miles, Kendall
stopped.

2975
03:20:15,510 --> 03:20:21,449
Magnetic bombs were washing his screen continuously
now, seeking to exhaust the ship as all the

2976
03:20:21,449 --> 03:20:24,550
great ships beyond poured their energy against
it.

2977
03:20:24,550 --> 03:20:30,279
A slow smile spread over Kendall's mouth as
he heard the gentle hum of the barely working

2978
03:20:30,279 --> 03:20:32,120
material-engine.

2979
03:20:32,120 --> 03:20:37,880
Carefully he aligned the nose UV beam of the
"S Doradus" on the nearest of the Miran ships.

2980
03:20:37,880 --> 03:20:41,270
Then he depressed a switch.

2981
03:20:41,270 --> 03:20:45,060
There was no ion-release before the force-mirror
now.

2982
03:20:45,060 --> 03:20:50,780
Just a jet of gas whirling into a half-inch
field of "Uncertainty of the Fourth Degree."

2983
03:20:50,780 --> 03:20:56,939
The matter vanished instantly in released
energy so stupendous that the greatest previous

2984
03:20:56,939 --> 03:21:01,960
UV beams had been harmless things by comparison.

2985
03:21:01,960 --> 03:21:05,130
Material energy maintained the mirror forces.

2986
03:21:05,130 --> 03:21:08,140
Material energy gave the power that was released.

2987
03:21:08,140 --> 03:21:12,590
And only material energy could have stood
up before it.

2988
03:21:12,590 --> 03:21:20,080
Thirty thousand miles away, a Miran ship flamed
instantaneously into inconceivable incandescence,

2989
03:21:20,080 --> 03:21:24,660
vanishing almost in blue-violet light of terrific
intensity.

2990
03:21:24,660 --> 03:21:28,439
The ship reeled away, a half-molten wreck.

2991
03:21:28,439 --> 03:21:33,410
The beam spotted two more ships before it
winked out.

2992
03:21:33,410 --> 03:21:36,279
Then Kendall began sending bombs.

2993
03:21:36,279 --> 03:21:40,359
He moved up to within 2000 miles that his
aim might be accurate.

2994
03:21:40,359 --> 03:21:46,399
They were bombs of "Uncertainty of the Third
Degree," the Uncertainty of atomic law in

2995
03:21:46,399 --> 03:21:48,659
bomb form.

2996
03:21:48,659 --> 03:21:53,210
One hit the nose of the nearest ship, and
a sphere five feet in diameter glowed mistily

2997
03:21:53,210 --> 03:21:55,330
blue for a moment.

2998
03:21:55,330 --> 03:22:00,460
Then very easily, the matter that formed the
wall of the cruiser began to run and change,

2999
03:22:00,460 --> 03:22:05,740
and presently there was only a hole, and an
expanding cloud of gas.

3000
03:22:05,740 --> 03:22:11,280
Three more flowed toward it—and the hole
enlarged, and another hole appeared in a bulkhead

3001
03:22:11,280 --> 03:22:13,850
behind.

3002
03:22:13,850 --> 03:22:15,370
Kendall made a change.

3003
03:22:15,370 --> 03:22:20,870
For the first time there came the staccato
bark of the material engine under strain,

3004
03:22:20,870 --> 03:22:26,920
as it fashioned the terrific fields of "Uncertainty
of the Ultimate Degree."

3005
03:22:26,920 --> 03:22:32,210
Abruptly they leapt out, invisible till they
entered a magnetic screen, then run over with

3006
03:22:32,210 --> 03:22:38,310
opalescent light as the energy of the field
was sucked into them and released.

3007
03:22:38,310 --> 03:22:43,560
It struck the nose of a ship—a field no
larger than an apple—

3008
03:22:43,560 --> 03:22:48,750
A titanic gout of energy burst out that was
soundless in space.

3009
03:22:48,750 --> 03:22:54,380
The ship suddenly opened back, opened like
the peel of a banana, till a little nub remained

3010
03:22:54,380 --> 03:23:00,580
at the further end, and the metal flaps dropped
back across and behind it dejectedly.

3011
03:23:00,580 --> 03:23:05,390
A second ship was struck, and it was struck
on one side, so that it was shattered like

3012
03:23:05,390 --> 03:23:08,630
a spent firecracker.

3013
03:23:08,630 --> 03:23:13,490
Then the Miran fleet vanished in speed.

3014
03:23:13,490 --> 03:23:14,640
Kendall followed them.

3015
03:23:14,640 --> 03:23:20,229
"I think," he said with a grin, "they tried
to use their radio beam, but it spread too

3016
03:23:20,229 --> 03:23:22,069
much to do anything at that distance.

3017
03:23:22,069 --> 03:23:26,350
And they used their rotating magnetic field,
which we couldn't feel.

3018
03:23:26,350 --> 03:23:28,490
And their crumbler ray too, of course.

3019
03:23:28,490 --> 03:23:32,479
I wonder—are they headed only for Jupiter?

3020
03:23:32,479 --> 03:23:35,399
No—no, they've passed it!"

3021
03:23:35,399 --> 03:23:41,000
Faster than light, faster than energy could
follow through space, or Uncertainty Bombs

3022
03:23:41,000 --> 03:23:44,970
pursue, the Mirans were fleeing for home.

3023
03:23:44,970 --> 03:23:49,040
They knew now that only in speed lay safety.

3024
03:23:49,040 --> 03:23:53,229
Already they knew that a similar ship had
appeared off Jupiter, and, after wiping out

3025
03:23:53,229 --> 03:23:58,210
the Phobos and Mars stations with one bomb
each, had cleared the Jovian Satellites with

3026
03:23:58,210 --> 03:24:01,350
equal terrible efficiency.

3027
03:24:01,350 --> 03:24:06,290
In one of the fleeing ships was a broken,
tired old man, and his staff.

3028
03:24:06,290 --> 03:24:12,180
Gresth Gkae looked back at the blank, distorted
space behind them, at the swiftly dwindling

3029
03:24:12,180 --> 03:24:13,989
sun, and spoke.

3030
03:24:13,989 --> 03:24:16,370
"I was at fault, my friends.

3031
03:24:16,370 --> 03:24:18,200
Jarth has spoken.

3032
03:24:18,200 --> 03:24:21,399
They are the stronger and the wiser race.

3033
03:24:21,399 --> 03:24:27,220
Farth Skalt has shown you—they use space
fields of intensity 100.

3034
03:24:27,220 --> 03:24:30,340
That means the energy of the ultimate destruction.

3035
03:24:30,340 --> 03:24:37,120
Jarth used us as his instrument of testing,
only to drive and stimulate that race.

3036
03:24:37,120 --> 03:24:38,279
I do not—nay.

3037
03:24:38,279 --> 03:24:41,779
There is no doubt now, for look."

3038
03:24:41,779 --> 03:24:46,479
Plainly visible, rapidly overtaking them,
the "S Doradus" appeared sharp, and luminous

3039
03:24:46,479 --> 03:24:49,069
on the jet of distorted space.

3040
03:24:49,069 --> 03:24:52,109
"We cannot escape, my friends.

3041
03:24:52,109 --> 03:24:56,300
Shall we return to Sthor or remain in space,
lost?"

3042
03:24:56,300 --> 03:25:00,970
"Let us deflect our course—at least he may
not know our destination."

3043
03:25:00,970 --> 03:25:05,720
The interstellar ship turned very slightly
in her course.

3044
03:25:05,720 --> 03:25:12,950
Plainly they saw the "S Doradus" flash on,
in a straight line, headed for distant, red-glowing

3045
03:25:12,950 --> 03:25:14,029
Mira.

3046
03:25:14,029 --> 03:25:17,819
Gresth Gkae watched, and shrugged.

3047
03:25:17,819 --> 03:25:22,660
Silently he put the ship back on its course,
at its utmost speed.

3048
03:25:22,660 --> 03:25:26,340
Parallel with them, near to them, the "S Doradus"
flashed on.

3049
03:25:26,340 --> 03:25:31,260
Day after day, the two hurled through space
faster than light.

3050
03:25:31,260 --> 03:25:35,700
Gradually Mira brightened, and at last became
a disc.

3051
03:25:35,700 --> 03:25:41,479
Gresth Gkae slowed his ships, and Kendall,
watching, slowed to match his speed.

3052
03:25:41,479 --> 03:25:45,870
Five billion miles from Sthor, they had reached
normal space speeds.

3053
03:25:45,870 --> 03:25:49,620
Viciously the Miran fleet attacked the lone
ship from Earth.

3054
03:25:49,620 --> 03:25:53,640
Their rays, their bombs, their every weapon
was flaming.

3055
03:25:53,640 --> 03:25:58,270
Great interstellar ships flashed suddenly
into speeds greater than that of light, seeking

3056
03:25:58,270 --> 03:26:01,800
to ram and destroy the smaller ship.

3057
03:26:01,800 --> 03:26:07,310
The "S Doradus" flashed into equal or greater
speed, and eluded them.

3058
03:26:07,310 --> 03:26:11,370
Kendall had determined now, which was the
leader's ship.

3059
03:26:11,370 --> 03:26:17,710
Gresth Gkae watched dully as his ships attempted
to destroy the single, small ship.

3060
03:26:17,710 --> 03:26:23,020
He sighed in resignation, and turned to walk
back to the chapel aboard the ship.

3061
03:26:23,020 --> 03:26:26,280
One last prayer to Jarth—

3062
03:26:26,280 --> 03:26:28,930
Gresth Gkae stopped abruptly.

3063
03:26:28,930 --> 03:26:31,410
The great ship was lurching strangely.

3064
03:26:31,410 --> 03:26:35,080
Men shouted sudden, frightened cries.

3065
03:26:35,080 --> 03:26:38,510
The clanking and thud of relays sounded, the
shrill of alarms.

3066
03:26:38,510 --> 03:26:44,520
Then the alarms stopped, and suddenly the
whole great ship vibrated to an infinitely

3067
03:26:44,520 --> 03:26:48,159
deep voice speaking in perfect Sthorian.

3068
03:26:48,159 --> 03:26:54,020
The voice remarked solemnly, in great, vibrant
tones, that they would certainly receive news

3069
03:26:54,020 --> 03:26:56,660
presently from the Expeditions.

3070
03:26:56,660 --> 03:27:01,770
It went on for some seconds to discuss the
conditions as reported in the new system.

3071
03:27:01,770 --> 03:27:04,380
Then it stopped abruptly.

3072
03:27:04,380 --> 03:27:10,160
An electric motor just above Gresth Gkae's
head suddenly hummed into action without reason

3073
03:27:10,160 --> 03:27:12,540
or power connection.

3074
03:27:12,540 --> 03:27:17,979
Almost simultaneously he heard the shouts
of startled men as the great lock doors began

3075
03:27:17,979 --> 03:27:23,560
to open into space of their own accord, bulkhead
doors slipped shut as the roar of escaping

3076
03:27:23,560 --> 03:27:26,159
air echoed in the ship.

3077
03:27:26,159 --> 03:27:29,020
Then it was all over.

3078
03:27:29,020 --> 03:27:32,479
Gresth Gkae ran to the control room.

3079
03:27:32,479 --> 03:27:35,479
The Mirans there looked up at him with drawn
faces.

3080
03:27:35,479 --> 03:27:38,470
"The instruments—Gresth Gkae—the instruments.

3081
03:27:38,470 --> 03:27:47,400
The instruments read impossible things, the
motors worked without reason, the fields fluctuated—the

3082
03:27:47,400 --> 03:27:52,050
atomic engines stopped and the magnetic shield
broke down and gripped part of the ship instead!"

3083
03:27:52,050 --> 03:27:54,540
reported the bewildered pilot.

3084
03:27:54,540 --> 03:28:00,790
"I do not know—some strange weapon of—"
began the old scientist.

3085
03:28:00,790 --> 03:28:06,920
Something luminous and huge twisted suddenly
through space toward them, a bomb of "Uncertainty

3086
03:28:06,920 --> 03:28:08,229
of the First Degree."

3087
03:28:08,229 --> 03:28:13,900
It wrapped the ship silently—and again strange
things happened.

3088
03:28:13,900 --> 03:28:19,460
Abruptly the ship started whirling violently,
yet without centrifugal force.

3089
03:28:19,460 --> 03:28:24,780
The heavens wheeled crazily, and turned about
three axes simultaneously.

3090
03:28:24,780 --> 03:28:29,560
There was no gyroscopic effect to hold them!

3091
03:28:29,560 --> 03:28:31,069
Gradually the thing died out.

3092
03:28:31,069 --> 03:28:37,480
Then a great field seemed to catch the ship,
and hurl it away from its companions.

3093
03:28:37,480 --> 03:28:40,930
Abruptly the pilot applied all his power to
pull free.

3094
03:28:40,930 --> 03:28:42,199
In vain.

3095
03:28:42,199 --> 03:28:47,479
Gresth Gkae shook his head slowly, and raised
the pilot's hands from the board.

3096
03:28:47,479 --> 03:28:50,189
"Let them do as they will.

3097
03:28:50,189 --> 03:28:53,779
I think they mean us no real harm, Thart Kralt.

3098
03:28:53,779 --> 03:28:56,311
They can, we know, destroy us in an instant.

3099
03:28:56,311 --> 03:29:04,229
Perhaps he wants us to go somewhere with him"—Gresth
Gkae smiled sadly—"and anyway, we can do

3100
03:29:04,229 --> 03:29:06,189
nothing."

3101
03:29:06,189 --> 03:29:11,560
For nearly a billion miles the great ship
was hurled through space at tremendous normal-space

3102
03:29:11,560 --> 03:29:12,680
velocity.

3103
03:29:12,680 --> 03:29:17,479
Then abruptly it was halted, without a sign
of strain or hurt.

3104
03:29:17,479 --> 03:29:22,520
The great twenty-foot UV beam on the nose
of the "S Doradus" broke into glowing gentle

3105
03:29:22,520 --> 03:29:23,520
red light.

3106
03:29:23,520 --> 03:29:25,680
It flashed twice.

3107
03:29:25,680 --> 03:29:27,620
There was a pause.

3108
03:29:27,620 --> 03:29:29,980
Then it flashed four times.

3109
03:29:29,980 --> 03:29:31,930
A long wait.

3110
03:29:31,930 --> 03:29:36,659
Then three times, a pause and nine times.

3111
03:29:36,659 --> 03:29:38,439
A wait.

3112
03:29:38,439 --> 03:29:41,670
Four times, a pause, sixteen times.

3113
03:29:41,670 --> 03:29:44,500
Then it stopped.

3114
03:29:44,500 --> 03:29:49,590
A slow smile of ineffable joy spread over
Gresth Gkae's face.

3115
03:29:49,590 --> 03:29:52,180
"Jarth Be Praised.

3116
03:29:52,180 --> 03:29:55,550
He can destroy, but does not wish to.

3117
03:29:55,550 --> 03:30:02,220
Ah, Thart Kralt, turn your spotlight toward
him, and flash it twenty-five times, for he

3118
03:30:02,220 --> 03:30:05,150
is trying to start communications with us.

3119
03:30:05,150 --> 03:30:08,470
Jarth is wise beyond all understanding.

3120
03:30:08,470 --> 03:30:12,860
They were the weaker race, and they are the
stronger.

3121
03:30:12,860 --> 03:33:13,659
But also they are the better, for they could
destroy, and they do not, but seek only 

3122
03:33:13,659 --> 03:33:24,290
to communicate."

3123
03:33:24,290 --> 03:33:32,030
- THE END -

